oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Gen. Pershing reviewing troops
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: In this photograph Gen. John J. Pershing is seen on a white horse and reviewing troops from III Corps at Vallendar, Germany. Vallendar is misspelled as Vallondor on the back of the photograph. The photograph belonged to Maj. John Ring, 308th Eng. Battn. Three Ring brothers served in World War I. They were from Franklin, Williamson County, Tennessee.
